# Improved AI Agent Coding Guidelines

## API & Interface Integrity
- **Preserve public APIs** — Never break existing public interfaces.
- **Maintain trait implementations** — Only modify `impl Render`; all other trait implementations must remain unchanged when possible.

## Code Quality Standards
- **Prioritize conciseness** — Write minimal, efficient code.
- **Maintain consistency** — Match existing code style and patterns exactly when possible.
- **Design for reusability** — Create modular, composable solutions.

## Modification Best Practices
- **Minimize new code** — Leverage existing functionality before adding new implementations.
- **Refactor when expanding** — When adding substantial code, improve the existing structure rather than just appending
- **Document sparingly** — Add comments only for non-obvious logic or when explicitly requested.

## Quick Reference Format

```
✓ DO:
  - Preserve public APIs
  - Match existing style
  - Refactor during expansion
  - Write reusable components
  - Keep changes minimal

✗ DON'T:
  - Break interfaces
  - Change traits (except Render)
  - Add unnecessary comments
  - Introduce inconsistent patterns
  - Write redundant code
```